1.1.description:
Instalation node.js

<pre><code>npm install loggy
</code></pre>

<p>See example/server.js if you want to use cluster or</p>

<pre><code>var app = require("Loggy");
app.listen(3000);
console.log("Loggy server listening on port %d", app.address().port);
</code></pre>

Usage

<p>Visit localhost:3000 install bookmarklet and activate it on wordpress installation(login to it first as admin). Then where you want to use it</p>

<pre><code>global $Loggy;
$Loggy-&#62;debug(string..array..object);    
$Loggy-&#62;info(string..array..object);
</code></pre>

